<br>
IIRC Greenhouse effect works by trapping certain frequencys of re-emitted infra-red. The point is (and this is from Sir Fred Hoyle FRCS BTW) that even very low levels of CO2 provide an almost total block to the infra-red frequencies affected.  Increacing the amount of CO2 wont trap significantly more heat unless the levels rise *very* considerably.  <br>
<br>
Putting thicker glass in your garden greenhouse wont make it any hotter for precisly the same reason!<br>
<br>
It is certainly true that there are other man-made chemicals which are capable of trapping infra-red at frequencys not previously trapped naturally and perhaps these are more of a problem.<br>
<br>
in any case, There are plenty of other reasons to reduce our dependence on fossil fuels but I am not convinced about this one.<br>
<br>
