Near the poles tundra melts which relieces even more CO2 and Methane..<br>
<br>
Thus the rise in the &quot;Alleged&quot; greenhouse gasses is not causing the climate change, it is a consiqurence of it!<br>
<br>
(similarly, a climate cooling would reverse each of these effects and new forest growth could mop up CO2 and cause CO2 levels to fall)<br>
<br>
If global warming models are based mainly on these sort of historic statistics then we are running a great risk of barking up completly the wrong tree, The worst case scenarion could be that we may be spending billions (hundreds of billions!) of dollars trying to solve a problem that doesn't exist.<br>
<br>
<br>
Please note, I am not claiming that there isnt climate change going on, Neither am I claiming that this wont cause problems. its just that I think we may be better off spending our resources on coping with the consiquences rather than squandering them on futile attemps at preventing the inevitable.<br>
